'''Yuki Shrine''' (ゆきじんじゃ) is a shrine listed in the {{ill|lt=Engishiki Jinmyōchō|Q11064932|WD=Q11064932|lt=Engishiki Shikinaisha|1=Engishiki Jinmyōchō}} located in Shitoda, {{ill|lt=Tomiya City|Q1205173|WD=Q1205173|1=Tomiya, Miyagi}}, {{ill|lt=Miyagi Prefecture|Q47896|WD=Q47896|1=Miyagi Prefecture}}.<ref name=jinjacho>{{Cite web|Japanese|url=http://www.town.tomiya.miyagi.jp/html/shuyu/index3.html|title=Tomiya City / Tomiya Shūyū|publisher=Tomiya City|accessdate=2015-03-09}}</ref>

=== Overview ===
The northern part of Tomiya City is characterized by expansive {{ill|UNKNOWN|lt=rice paddies|1=UNKNOWN}}, and the shrine stands atop a hill about 300 meters from a side road west of {{ill|lt=National Route 4|Q1055023|WD=Q1055023|1=Japan National Route 4}}, at the eastern edge of the {{ill|lt=hills|Q222912|WD=Q222912|1=Hügelland}} in the Shitoda area to the northwest. It is one of the Shikinaisha shrines, of which there were one hundred in the former {{ill|lt=Mutsu Province|Q907389|WD=Q907389|1=Mutsu Province}} and four in {{ill|lt=Kurokawa District|Q1131782|WD=Q1131782|1=Kurokawa District, Miyagi}}. During the {{ill|lt=Daijōsai|Q11433653|WD=Q11433653|1=Daijosai}}, two temporary halls—the Yuki-den and the Suki-den—are specially constructed to the east and west, where the ritual ceremonies are conducted. There is also a theory that considers the shrine’s significance in connection with Suki Shrine, which is enshrined in {{ill|lt=Ōhira Village|Q1204681|WD=Q1204681|1=Ōhira, Miyagi}} to the north of this shrine. Within the precincts stands a cedar tree approximately 20 meters tall with a trunk circumference of over 3 meters, estimated to be more than 700 years old.

=== Nearby Shrines ===
* {{ill|lt=Kashima Amatariwake Shrine|Q20043641|WD=Q20043641|1=Kashima Amatarashiwake Shrine}} – 2-16 Wada, Ōgama, Tomiya City  
* {{ill|lt=Kumano Shrine (Tomiya City)|Q28690106|WD=Q28690106|1=Kumano Shrine}} – 16 Shimmachi, Tomiya, Tomiya City  
* Ninomiya Shrine – 92 Tatenoshita, Ninoseki, Tomiya City  
* {{ill|lt=Hachiman Shrine (Yamato Town)|Q22119988|WD=Q22119988|lt=Yoshioka Hachiman Shrine|1=Hachiman Shrine}} – 39 Machiura, Aza Yoshioka, {{ill|lt=Yamato Town|Q1205377|WD=Q1205377|1=Taiwa, Miyagi}}, Kurokawa District  
* '''Suki Shrine''' – 4 Shimomiyamae, Aza Komaba, Kurokawa District, Ōhira Village  
* {{ill|lt=Ōhira Hachiman Shrine|Q11438808|WD=Q11438808|1=Ōhira Hachiman Shrine}} – 48 Hachiman, Aza Ōhira, Kurokawa District

=== Access ===
* About 10 minutes by car from {{ill|lt=Tōhoku Expressway|Q428428|WD=Q428428|1=Tōhoku Expressway}} {{ill|lt=Yamato Interchange|Q10934247|WD=Q10934247|lt=Yamato IC|1=Taiwa interchange}}
* About 10 minutes by car from {{ill|lt=Sendai-Hokubu Road|Q11377788|WD=Q11377788|1=Sendai-Hokubu Road}} {{ill|lt=Tomiya Interchange|Q16144881|WD=Q16144881|lt=Tomiya IC|1=Tomiya interchange}}
* About 20 minutes by car from {{ill|lt=Tōhoku Expressway|Q428428|WD=Q428428|1=Tōhoku Expressway}} {{ill|lt=Izumi Interchange|Q11143029|WD=Q11143029|lt=Izumi IC|1=Izumi interchange}}

